CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 21, 1962, pg. A5 reads: "Cited By Kay Club - Bailey Gordon (second from right), a member of the board of management of Kay Boys Club, presents citations to three area leaders during the recent dinner meeting of the club's religious education department. Left to right: Dr. John Hare, pastor of Grandview United Presbyterian Church; Dr. John Galbreath, pastor of Westminister United Presbyterian Church; Mr. Gordon and Benjamin Moore of the Social Security Administration. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Men and women seated at banquet tables, with head table on left including Dr. John Hare and Dr. John Galbreath seated on left end, and Benjamin Moore, third from right, in Kay Boy's Club for dinner meeting of the Religious Education Department
